 the data your backend passed over via ",[21,163,164],{},"name",", then uses ",[21,167,168],{},"id"," to store and output each row. There are a few other parameters too. Say you want the output to start from the second record — you'd use ",[21,171,172],{},"offset"," to set the starting point. And if you want to limit it to just one record (my table only has four rows right now), that's what ",[21,175,176],{},"length"," is for:",[36,179,181],{"className":38,"code":180,"language":40,"meta":41,"style":41},"{volist name=\"user\" id=\"list\" offset=\"2\" length=\"1\"}\n\u003Cul class=\"list-group\">\n  \u003Cli class=\"list-group-item active\">Name:{$list.name}\u003C\u002Fli>\n  \u003Cli class=\"list-group-item\">Weight:{$list.weight}\u003C\u002Fli>\n  \u003Cli class=\"list-group-item\">Height:{$list.height}\u003C\u002Fli>\n\u003C\u002Ful>\n{\u002Fvolist}\n",[21,182,183,188,202,220,238,256,264],{"__ignoreMap":41},[45,184,185],{"class":47,"line":48},[45,186,187],{"class":51},"{volist name=\"user\" id=\"list\" offset=\"2\" length=\"1\"}\n",[45,189,190,192,194,196,198,200],{"class":47,"line":55},[45,191,58],{"class":51},[45,193,62],{"class":61},[45,195,66],{"class":65},[45,197,69],{"class":51},[45,199,73],{"class":72},[45,201,76],{"class":51},[45,203,204,206,208,210,212,214,216,218],{"class":47,"line":79},[45,205,82],{"class":51},[45,207,85],{"class":61},[45,209,66],{"class":65},[45,211,69],{"class":51},[45,213,92],{"class":72},[45,215,95],{"class":51},[45,217,85],{"class":61},[45,219,76],{"class":51},[45,221,222,224,226,228,230,232,234,236],{"class":47,"line":102},[45,223,82],{"class":51},[45,225,85],{"class":61},[45,227,66],{"class":65},[45,229,69],{"class":51},[45,231,113],{"class":72},[45,233,116],{"class":51},[45,235,85],{"class":61},[45,237,76],{"class":51},[45,239,240,242,244,246,248,250,252,254],{"class":47,"line":123},[45,241,82],{"class":51},[45,243,85],{"class":61},[45,245,66],{"class":65},[45,247,69],{"class":51},[45,249,113],{"class":72},[45,251,136],{"class":5