1173,27],{},"Personally though, I don't recommend doing this. It tends to cause maintenance headaches down the line, so I'd still go with ",[21,1174,23],{},[12,1176,1178],{"id":1177},"wrap-up","Wrap-up",[17,1180,1181,1182,1184,1185,1187,1188,1190,1191,1193,1194,1201],{},"This post covered the three looping tags ThinkPHP gives you: ",[21,1183,23],{},", ",[21,1186,783],{},", and ",[21,1189,858],{},". In practice though, you'll mostly just reach for ",[21,1192,23],{}," — as you can see from the examples above, it's more capable and more convenient. For a more detailed rundown, check out the ",[1195,1196,1200],"a",{"href":1197,"rel":1198},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.kancloud.cn\u002Fmanual\u002Fthinkphp5_1\u002F354084",[1199],"nofollow","loop tags chapter"," in the official manual (page in Mandarin).",[1203,1204,1205],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sKpQp, html code.shiki .sKpQp{--shiki-default:#72F088}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .sj_SG, html code.shiki .sj_SG{--shiki-default:#DBB7FF}",{"title":41,"searchDepth":55,"depth":55,"links":1207},[1208,1209,1210,1211,1212],{"id":14,"depth":55,"text":15},{"id":30,"depth":55,"text":31},{"id":776,"depth":55,"text":777},{"id":848,"depth":55,"text":849},{"id":1177,"depth":55,"text":1178},"PHP","2019-09-22 00:01:20","We've actually been using a few of ThinkPHP's built-in template tags in earlier chapters, like volist, but I never stopped to explain what they actually do. So this kicks off a small series on the built-in tags. First up: the three looping tags. We'll cover volist (the powerful one), the simple for loop, and foreach — including the parameters like offset, length, empty, and key that make volist so handy.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002Fthinkphp-day-21-built-in-tags-01","4",{"title":6,"description":1215},false,"en\u002FPHP\u002Fthinkphp-day-21-built-in-tags-01",[1213,1226,1227,1228,1229],"MySQL","ThinkPHP 5.1","Learning ThinkPHP from Scratch","iThome Ironman Contest",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F22\u002Fthinkphp-day-21-built-in-tags-01\u002F","Rh2RshYRX68_jEfik9yaCDBXVou_mNAvHN9NVhht_ws",{"newer":1234,"older":1238},{"url":1235,"title":1236,"date":1237},"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F23\u002Fthink-php-day-22-builtin-tags-02\u002F","ThinkPHP from Scratch Day 22 - Comparison & Conditional Tags","2019-09-23 00:01:06",{"url":1239,"title":1240,"date":1241},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F22\u002Fre-learning-js-from-zero-07-functions\u002F","Re:Learning JS From Zero — Day 7: Functions, Your Reusable Code Wrappers","2019-09-22 00:01:10",[1243,1247,1252],{"url":1244,"title":1245,"date":1246,"readingMinutes":840},"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fmac-xampp-apache-wont-start-fix\u002F","Fixing Mac XAMPP Apache Won't Start","2022-04-17 14:32:41",{"url":1248,"title":1249,"date":1250,"readingMinutes":1251},"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F02\u002Fthinkphp-day-31-the-end-is-just-another-beginning\u002F","Day 31 - Learning ThinkPHP From Scratch: The End Is Just Another Beginning","2019-10-02 00:00:02","3",{"url":1253,"title":1254,"date":1255,"readingMinutes":1221},"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F01\u002Fthinkphp-day-30-deploy-to-heroku\u002F","Day 30 - Learning ThinkPHP f